<DOC><DOCNO> AP880321-0053 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-21-88 0720EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Japan-Attack     03-21 0112</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Japan-Attack,0114</SECOND><HEAD>Motorcycle Explodes In Downtown Tokyo</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A motorcycle that may have been laden withexplosives blew up in downtown Tokyo today, damaging windows ofnearby buildings but causing no injuries, police reported.   A police official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said theexplosion occurred near Hibiya Park about 880 yards southeast ofthe Imperial Palace. He said the motorcycle appeared to have beenrigged with explosives.   He said there were reports of explosions in three other parts ofthe city and that authorities are investigating the incidents.   The official said Japanese radicals might have been responsiblefor the motorcycle explosion, but details were not immediatelyavailable.</TEXT></DOC>